Origin of the name Millicent: Derived from the obsolete Old High German Amalswinth, a compound name composed of the elements amal (work) and swinth (strength). The name was brought to England by the Normans in the French forms Melisent and Melisende. From A World of Baby Names by Teresa Norman.

Millicent /mil-li-cent/ [3 sylls.] as a girls' name is pronounced MIL-a-sent. It is of Old French origin, and the meaning of Millicent is brave strength. Norman name. American Congresswoman Millicent Fenwick.
